MatchedRegions.transcript: In our experiments, the evaluated UDA methods achieved a maximum accuracy gain of around 4% and high positives and negative rates.
This shows that the methods are not able to achieve comparable results to the supervised baselines.
Furthermore, we observe FP and FN rates increase significantly on the multi-target task of MuLane.

MatchedRegion.Text: FP and FN rates increase significantly on the multi-target task of MuLane

MatchedRegions.transcript: We want to emphasize that FP and FN represent strongly detected and missing lanes, which can lead to crucial impacts on autonomous driving.

MatchedRegion.Text: FP and FN represent wrongly detected and missing lanes, which can lead to crucial impacts on autonomous driving functions
